FRC#2022 is currently redesigning our programming curriculum, and we’d like some feedback.

docs.google.com

AY26 Programming Curriculum for feedback

AY26 programming curriculum for feedback FRC#2022 members should see . General ideas Host it in a meeting room with lots of outlets and no corners to hide in Start second week of Q1 Exercises should have high ceiling but low bar – should be easy to...

This is designed to be taught by a small group of students (we have no programming mentor), but is probably longer than is feasible. However, we don’t have students with experience in many of the important topics from previous seasons, and we only serve students for three years, so we need to build up enough knowledge for the build season from a lower level.
